bug.short_desc: Loading fails with minimum boot package

long_desc.thetext: Our current loading process is currently based on some assumptions like having the qx.event.handler.Application in the boot part. If thats not the case, there can be some timing situations where the startup of the app fails in IE.

(In reply to comment #1) > Here is our solution to fix the problem > > run : function() > ...
The fix should be added to qooxdoo. qx.$$loader should check if the qx.event.handler.Application class is already available. If the class was not available in qx.$$loader another class (e.g. Part, when new parts are loaded) should always perform the check if qx.event.handler.Application is available and if so, execute the qx.event.handler.Application.onScriptLoaded(); function. Another thing to consider is that in qx.core.Init.ready(); function rely on an existing Application class. The Application class might be not available in the part were qx.event.handler.Application is included. When this happens the application is already ready, but not executed (this could also happen when another startup hook takes effect). Thats why we have to make a check when the application is ready and execute the qx.core.Init.ready function.
Created attachment 753 Here is the skeleton based application to reproduce the issue.
Tested it and our application starts just fine. Thanks!
